article.headline: Fordham 88, N.J. Tech 44
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Brenton Butler scored 21 points and Fordham kept New Jersey Tech winless this season with an 88-44 victory Saturday. Marcus Stout had 16 points the Rams (5-4), who led 41-21 at halftime, while Mike Moore added 14 and Bryant Dunston 13. Nesho Milosevic had 12 points for the Highlanders (0-11), while Justin Garris added 10. Mike Binn's two free throws capped Fordham's game-opening 13-2 run and the closest the Highlanders got the rest of the way was 22-14 on Kyle Edwards' layup with 10:35 left in the first half. Dunston's jumper with 3:59 to play gave Fordham its biggest lead, 84-40.
